trans-unit.source: The SearchResponse class is sent by the server as a response to a <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchRequest"></xref> object.

This response contains zero or more <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultEntry"></xref> objects, and zero or more <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReference"></xref> objects.
The Controls property contains the <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryControl"></xref> object returned by the server.
The <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.DirectoryControl"></xref> object returned by the server.
The Entries property contains a <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultEntryCollection"></xref> object that contains the entries returned by the search.
A <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultEntryCollection"></xref> object that contains the entries returned by the search.
The ErrorMessage property contains the error message, if any, for this operation.
The error message, if any, for this operation.
The MatchedDN property contains the matched distinguished name returned by the server.
The matched distinguished name returned by the server.
The References property contains a <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection"></xref> object that contains search references returned by the server.
A <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.SearchResultReferenceCollection"></xref> object that contains search references returned by the server.
The Referral property contains the server referrals.
The ResultCode property contains a value of <xref href="System.DirectoryServices.Protocols.ResultCode"></xref> that specifies the result code for the operation.
The result code for the operation.
